Simplest solution could be to split your number in 2 parts - given pattern and rest bits. Let&#39;s say biggest number is 5 bits long and given pattern is 3 - &#39;101&#39;, so remaining part is 2 bits. Then you enumerate all variants for 2 bits and create numbers using them and joining with target pattern with all variants  -

    00 gives you &#39;00 101&#39; &#39;0 101 0&#39; &#39;101 00&#39;
    01 gives you &#39;01 101&#39; &#39;0 101 0&#39; &#39;101 01&#39;
    10 gives you &#39;10 101&#39; &#39;1 101 0&#39; &#39;101 10&#39;
    11 gives you &#39;11 101&#39; &#39;1 101 1&#39; &#39;101 11&#39;

then you just eliminate duplicates and limit range.

